        "content": "<p>I am trying to introduce a pre-commit-hooks check to stop user from pushing to remote if mal-formatted code found in the changes, the most promising checker I have found is <a href=\"https://github.com/editorconfig-checker/editorconfig-checker\">https://github.com/editorconfig-checker/editorconfig-checker</a>, while it doesn't honor the .editorconfig already there in the repo, it seems to be using its own set of rules</p>",
        "id": 440403076,
        "sender_full_name": "Hao Liu",
        "timestamp": 1716500350
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Looks like it <a href=\"https://github.com/editorconfig-checker/editorconfig-checker/blob/dd3d0a712aa4171c404b80f235cfcafbec5ff20b/README.md?plain=1#L37\">supports <code>.editorconfig</code> file</a>?</p>",
        "id": 440404678,
